.SH NAME
bb-pr-task-edit - Edit a pull request task


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pr task edit  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Edit the body of a Bitbucket pull request task. Tasks are addressed by numeric task ID together with --pr \&.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--body\fP=""
	Task body text

.PP
\fB--body-file\fP=""
	Read the task body from a file, or '-' for stdin

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for edit

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--pr\fP=""
	Parent pull request as an ID or Bitbucket pull request URL

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pr task edit 3 --pr 1 --repo workspace-slug/repo-slug --body 'Updated follow-up'
  bb pr task edit 3 --pr https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1 --body-file task.md --json '*'
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbb-pr-task(1)\fP


